Flow: 

Limit service 
	/limits - controller - mapped by GET req - go to configuration class - @ConfigurationProperties("limits-service")
	go to props - sees config mapped - check for config app - through config (1) - takes the value from gir repo

Config-service	
	In parallel, config service has @EnableConfigServer - from propertiesfile- take the link and talks to local repo
	gets the value from repo based on service name (Including env)
	
	Config should be in running state and should render the values. Then only our service can take those and access


	   
